The Kwara State Government, on Friday, confirmed the resignation of former Commissioner for Special Duties, Hajia Aisha Ahman Pategi. In a two-paragraph statement in Ilorin, the state Communications Commissioner, Mrs Afolabi Oshatimehin said “The government has received the resignation of Hon Aisha Ahman Pategi, who was the former Commissioner for Special Duties. “The government accepts same and wishes her the best in her future endeavours,” the statement added. DAILY POST recalls that the former Commissioner for Special Duties resigned her appointment on Friday. Aisha, in a statement announcing her resignation, said ” I Aisha Ahman Pategi, the outgoing Commissioner for Special Duties, effective from today Friday, 28th August,2020, humbly wish to formally announce my resignation from the cabinet of His Excellency Governor Abdulrahman Abdulrazaq.” She thanked God Almighty, for giving her the grace and opportunity to serve as Commissioner for Local Government and Chieftaincy Affairs and now exciting as Commissioner for Special Duties, serving my fellow Kwarans and representing Pategi Local Government in our drive to better the lot of Kwarans. Aisha, at the inception of Governor Abdulrahman Abdulrazaq administration, was appointed as Commissioner for Local Government and Chieftaincy Affairs, before her redeployment to the Ministry of Special Duties following a minor cabinet reshuffle by the state governor.